    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix protocol timer tracing in PUCCH interference estimation\n\n### Summary\nThe `calc_pucch_1x_interference` function in the LTE eNB PHY layer was missing VCD signal dumper function tracing calls, which serve as protocol timers to track function execution. This caused incomplete tracing of PUCCH processing procedures.\n\nThis fix adds the missing VCD function tracing calls at the entry and exit points of the `calc_pucch_1x_interference` function to properly track its execution timing.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_TRANSPORT/pucch.c`: Added VCD signal dumper function tracing calls at the beginning and end of `calc_pucch_1x_interference` function using `VCD_SIGNAL_DUMPER_FUNCTIONS_PHY_PROCEDURES_ENB_RX_UESPEC`.\n\n### Reproduction\nWithout this fix, VCD traces will show incomplete timing information for PUCCH interference estimation procedures. Users analyzing protocol timing through VCD dumps may observe missing function entry/exit markers for this specific function, making it difficult to accurately measure execution time and identify performance bottlenecks in the PUCCH processing chain.\n"
}